snippet: The steamer Empire State, from Fall River for New-York, was run into by the schooner H. H. Tallman, from Alexandria for Dighton, last night, near Fort Adams. The schooner had her bowsprit, jib-boom and head carried away, and is leaky....
lead_paragraph: The steamer Empire State, from Fall River for New-York, was run into by the schooner H. H. Tallman, from Alexandria for Dighton, last night, near Fort Adams. The schooner had her bowsprit, jib-boom and head carried away, and is leaky.
